(2836, 139, 'artist_bio', 'BAFTA and Emmy Award winning New York born artist Drew Berry is one of the world\'s foremost 3D and 4D digital animators working in biomedical visualisation. Moving to Australia to complete a Bachelor and Master of Science at the University of Melbourne, he focused his later studies on human cells using time-lapse microscopy. Having conducted innovative medical research at the prestigious Walter and Eliza Hall Institute (WEHI) since 1995, his work concentrates on animating the behaviour, dynamics and physical properties of DNA, bio-molecules and proteins. Winner of the MacArthur Fellowship “Genius Award” in 2010, his animations have been exhibited at the Centre Georges Pompidou, Guggenheim Museum, MoMA, the University of Geneva, the Royal Institute of Great Britain, National Museum of Australia and ACMI. His work has featured in documentaries for the BBC, the American Museum of Natural History and in Björk’s music video for the track <i>Hollow</i>. A prolific guest speaker, Berry has presented at Vivid Sydney for their ideas programme, TEDx Talk in Sydney and at the SIGGRAPH computer graphics and interactive techniques conference in San Diego.'),
