(157, 3, '2013-11-22 02:45:34', '2013-11-22 02:45:34', 'Set to feature on the external walls of the National Gallery of Victoria, this White Night Melbourne commissioned projection work will celebrate Melbourne’s skin art. Paying homage to the ever-increasing popularity of tattoos both flaunted and hidden, the exploration and beauty of this art form has been embraced by our city. Images of tattooed Melburnians, up close and personal, will be revealed and transformed into digital projections.', 'Tattooed City', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '107-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 02:45:34', '2013-11-22 02:45:34', '', 107, 'http://whitenight.dev/107-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(158, 3, '2013-11-22 02:46:12', '2013-11-22 02:46:12', '<i>Tim Winton’s The Turning </i>is a unique cinema event created by award winning Melbourne based director-producer Robert Connolly. Eighteen directors from diverse artistic backgrounds each interpret one chapter of Tim Winton’s novel <i>The Turning</i>. Set in a small coastal community, stories link and overlap depicting important life changing moments for its central characters. As the book was inventively adapted for the screen, the film’s exhibition has also been reimagined in an extraordinary way. Each chapter will be staged in a different environment and location that relates to the core themes. With most sites kept a secret, audiences will discover an emotive screen trail engaging in a film experience like no other.', 'Tim Winton\'s The Turning', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '132-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-22 02:46:12', '2013-11-22 02:46:12', '', 132, 'http://whitenight.dev/132-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ;
